    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>
                <date>18 July. 5614</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>Rev Sir,    In page 230 of No 4 Vol 12 of the Occident,<lb/> appears an article
                headed <placeName>Louisville</placeName>, the <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>
                line of which<lb/> contains the following words:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">“it may suffer for a while from unfaithful leaders;”</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">As I am a candidate for the office, and as it<lb/> has been hinted
                by rivals &amp;c. that the above is<lb/> intended to apply to me, I would
                respectfully<lb/> ask you either privately or in your public capacity<lb/> as
                Editor, to state whether such construction<lb/> is intended thereby and if so, on
                what grounds<lb/> such assertion is founded.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I may be permitted to add that <hi rend="underline">I</hi><lb/> had
                no conception of so construing your language;<lb/> but am induced to address you in
                consequence<lb/> of the interpretation of others.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Entreating an early reply,</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Rev Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">respectfully Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">A. J. H. Bernal</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <placeName>226 Green St</placeName>
            </p>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <ref target="Occident_PDFs/Occ_12_4.pdf">The above text refers to Occident
                        Volume 12 No. 4 page 230. Click here to view.</ref>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
